      "author": "ppravdin",
      "description": "This update adds new ways to shape your dictation, and a friendly first-run setup.\n\nNew\n- Format as Markdown: turn what you say into a clean document with a title, headings, and bullet points. Inside a note that already has content, it fits what is there instead of adding a title.\n- More options in the new Enhance settings: Make English (speak any language, get English), Message ready (clean text for messages and email), Clean language (drop rough language), Content organize (reflow into tidy paragraphs and lists), and Technical vocabulary for developer terms.\n- A quick setup wizard the first time you connect. A few simple questions and it tunes everything to how you work. You can reopen it any time with Run setup again in settings.\n\nChanged\n- Settings are grouped into collapsible sections so they are easier to scan.\n- Spelling and word fixes now always run, so your text is cleaned up every time.\n- Removed the extra Create Account button. Sign In handles new accounts too.\n\nAs always, your audio is processed and then deleted, and your text stays on your device.\n",
      "downloadCount": 12,
      "draft": false,
